The Capitol was important as a strategical point. Thus it was held by Opimius against C. Gracchus, by Satur- ninus against the senate, by C. Manilius in 67 Β. Wirz supposes this to be the house of Milo, Anniana domus, mentioned Att. iv. 3. 3, which is more probably another name for the house on the Cermalus (i. e. on the Palatine near the Tiber), mentioned in the same passage. 10. referta: the construction is changed, arma, domus being nominatives, aster- wards summed up in haec sunt.
